  "text": "Lys cannot be aminoacylated inside mitochondria. Yet, as it can only bind to pre-MSK when aminoacylated, it is imported as a functional tRNA that can take part in protein synthesis, even though recycling is not possible. Interestingly, the other tRNA that is imported into mitochondria of S. cerevisiae, the tRNA Gln , is not co-imported with protein but by an as-yet-unknown mechanism [CITATION_1] .",
